==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Yex
<hw>Yex</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>⟦yogh⟧exen</ets>, <ets>yesken</ets>, AS. <ets>giscian</ets> to
sob.]</ety> <def>To hiccough.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>yox</asp>,
<asp>yux</asp>.]</altsp> <mark>[Obs. or Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He <qex>yexeth</qex> and he speaketh through the nose.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Yex</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Yex
